<section class="section">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow" data-i18n-key="demoFlow.eyebrow">Demo flow</p>
    <h2 data-i18n-key="demoFlow.title">Three shortest demo paths in the current release.</h2>
    <p data-i18n-key="demoFlow.body">Start with the smallest loop, then move into LAN or cross-network preview only when the demo needs it.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-grid">
    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="demoFlow.0.kind">Path 1</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="demoFlow.0.title">Single-machine</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="demoFlow.0.body">Run local-console and public-explorer on one machine to show signed profile flow, search, and verification badges.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="demoFlow.1.kind">Path 2</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="demoFlow.1.title">LAN two-machine</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="demoFlow.1.body">Use LAN preview to show peer discovery, online and offline transitions, and explorer search across devices on the same network.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="package-kind" data-i18n-key="demoFlow.2.kind">Path 3</p>
      <h3 data-i18n-key="demoFlow.2.title">Cross-network preview</h3>
      <p data-i18n-key="demoFlow.2.body">Use relay-backed preview when you want to show remote connectivity and discovery beyond a single local network.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
